        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>15. M. P. | Eastbourne</placeName>
                    <date>12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>One line to amend my request, if you try the C. of Ammonia experiment.— please drop the third drop on midrib of leaf on inside or upper side of leaf.—</p>
<p>Yours | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I am sorry that you have my Origin;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I hope you won’t think me bothersome, but would you like to have my Journal of Researches or Travels?<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. <hi rend="underline">like</hi> to send them to you.—</p>
<p>If Dionæa is allied in its moving apparatus &amp; whole structure to Drosera, as I suspect from what little I have yet seen; then the absorbing surface, wherever that may lie, would be shown by C. of Ammonia causing contraction; &amp; that is why I want you to try, middle parts of lateral disc &amp; midrib &amp; sensitive Hairs (&amp; <hi rend="underline">marginal Hairs</hi>?)</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">4.1 &amp; whole structure] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">4.4 parts] ‘p’ <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n3">4.4 sensitive] ‘si’ <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi></note>
                </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

